## Description
The&nbsp;**Respond Content (HTTP)**&nbsp;task allows to deliver the content processed by an on-demand application via HTTP.

> Note

This is the final task of all on-demand workflows.&nbsp;

It is possible to define multiple branches ending in multiple Respond content (HTTP) tasks, for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

In the&nbsp;**Alias**&nbsp;field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

### Filtering the content to be included in the response
To define one or more filtering rules for the files and folders to be included in the response:

- Select the connection line leading to the Respond Content (HTTP) task.

- In the configuration settings, enter one or more filename pattern filters. Of the previous task's output, only the files and folders matching the defined rules will be included in the response.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see:&nbsp;[Doxee Platform On-Demand Workflows User Manual](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-on-demand-workflows-user-manual).
